==English==
===Etymology===
The term '''ridiculous''' derives from the Latin word 'ridet', which literally translates into 
he, she, or it smiles or he, she, or it laughs.

===Adjective===
'''ridiculous'''
# Deserving of [[ridicule]]; [[foolish]].
# [[Absurd]].

